1. stored functions
    1.1. auth
        1.1.1. create user: user profile + user data + cross table
        1.1.2. create session
        1.1.3. get user by login for auth
        1.1.4. check if user exists by login
        1.1.5. update user data
        1.1.6. change user password/login
        1.1.7. update session data (close session)
        1.1.8. get full user data for profile popup
    1.2. categories
        1.2.1. create new category
        1.2.2. update existing category
        1.2.3. remove category
        1.2.4. get categories list
        1.2.5. get all categories
        1.2.6. get categories list for dropdown
    1.3. goods
        1.3.1. create new goods item
        1.3.2. update single existing goods item
        1.3.3. update multiple goods items
        1.3.4. remove goods item
        1.3.5. get goods slice / get all goods
        1.3.6. find top goods items by name
    1.4. purchases
        1.4.1. create new purchase: purchase data + cross table (goods details) + create new goods if not exist
        1.4.2. update existing purchase
        1.4.3. update goods details item
        1.4.4. remove existing purchase
        1.4.5. remove connection between goods and purchase (goods details records)
        1.4.6. get purchases slice / get all purchases
